    "abstractNote": "Adding to the Syriac witness on Genesis 3-4 introduced in Gary A. Anderson\u2019s monograph, <i>The Genesis of Perfection</i> (reviewed elsewhere in <i>Hugoye</i>) are two Syriac ascetical works: the Book of Steps (<i>Liber Graduum</i>), an anonymous 4th century collection of 30 <i>memre</i> directed to a pre-monastic community; and the 6th century collection of 13 <i>memre</i> or Discourses by Philoxenus, bishop of Mabbug, directed monks under his episcopal authority.  Both authors utilize the narrative of Genesis 3-4 to model ascetical practices for their community, and to portray the goal and reward of the ascetical life \u2013 the return to perfection in the Garden of Eden.",
